2026-07-10 breath: core-card reread, phase formulate

## Understanding restatement
v1 head = one workspace per machine; second project has no phone channel and a second
head collides on launchd labels. Router v1: ONE listener/digest pair per machine iterating
~/.qroky/registry (the ONE new file in ~, inside GATE-029's scope); events labeled
«[project]»; button press routes the decision record HOME; ONE merged digest; /status
across projects + name filter; free input without a project → ONE mechanical re-ask with
project buttons; human-level settings in ONE home; migration of the live v1 install with
ZERO questions (no re-bind, no second hello, no offset replay). NOT-DOING: multi-user,
per-project bots, topics, priorities, cross-machine registry.

## Design decisions (locked; each declared)
D1. HUMAN HOME (§3.7 pick): the PRIMARY workspace's telegram home — i.e. the FIRST
    registry entry's `<w>/.qroky/telegram/`. NOT a second file in ~/.qroky/ (GATE-029
    covers EXACTLY ONE file there: the registry). Resolution in lib.sh:
      TG_HOME = QROKY_TG_HOME || primary(registry)/.qroky/telegram || TG_LIB_DIR (v1)
      TG_ROOT = QROKY_TG_ROOT || primary(registry) || 3-up (v1)
    The env split becomes the routing: QROKY_TG_ROOT says «which project am I»,
    TG_HOME says «which human». A v1 install's existing home IS the primary home after
    migration — zero moves, zero re-asks. Documented in lib.sh header (H7).
D2. COMPAT SWITCH: router rendering (labels, merged digest, project re-ask) activates
    only when the registry holds >1 workspace. N∈{0,1} → byte-level v1 behavior — the
    15 existing scenarios stay green by construction, and a migrated single-project
    machine sees NOTHING change until a second project registers.
D3. MIGRATION AUTO-SEED (H5): listener pass, registry absent ∧ chat bound → write the
    registry with TG_ROOT as line 1 (atomic, mkdir -p). No sends, no bind writes, offset
    untouched. Registry absent ∧ unbound → no seed (fresh head; kit registers at install).
D4. ROUTING DATA PATH: pending-gates stay at HUMAN level and gain a `workspace:` line
    (queue entries serialize WORKSPACE too — flush preserves origin). pickup.sh reads it
    and passes --out-dir <origin>/decisions to the unchanged record-decision.sh — parity
    by construction untouched, exactly the INPUT §5 hint. gate-answer bus files stay in
    the human-level inbox; only the RECORD routes home (H1's assert target).
D5. FREE INPUT (multi only): name match against registry names (case-insensitive) →
    routed; no match → ONE mechanical re-ask with project buttons (id `route-<ts>`,
    callback `route-<ts>|<idx>`, labels+workspaces persisted in state/route-pending/<id>
    — same 64-byte discipline as gates; «общий» button appended when DEFAULT_PROJECT is
    set in the human profile). After the button (or a name match), the handler formulates
    and the task-proposal lands in the TARGET workspace's inbox (H4). Routed presses skip
    the LLM clarify — the human already answered one question; two asks would be nagging.
    The «кроки» kind keeps v1 semantics (machine-level gesture; folder routing is the
    skill's own business) — declared, not silent.
D6. DEAD PATHS (H6, the R2-1 lesson): every per-workspace iteration guards existence
    first; dead entry = one FLAG log line + a digest status line, never a crash, never a
    poison pill. unregister.sh removes cleanly.
D7. KIT HOOKS (perimeter: registration only + the recorded upgrade defect):
    (a) deploy → register.sh $WORKSPACE_DIR (idempotent);
    (b) second-workspace install with a bound primary on the machine → short-circuit:
        register only, honest «бот уже подключён — добавляю проект», no token/Start/
        second hello/second launchd pair (the collision INFO-034 diagnosed);
    (c) --apply-update auto-complete: token stored ∧ bound ∧ head present ∧ profile.conf
        absent → deploy + register, zero questions («токен есть, головы нет» folded);
        token stored ∧ NOT bound → one honest --enable-telegram hint (binding needs the
        human's Start — cannot be auto-completed, Rowan boundary).
    Kit harness gets per-scenario registry isolation (QROKY_REGISTRY per workdir) so the
    machine-level file does not couple unrelated scenarios through the shared fake HOME.
D8. register.sh/unregister.sh honor QROKY_REGISTRY (test override; production
    ~/.qroky/registry), canonicalize paths, comments/blank lines allowed.

## Harness-checklist (INFO-025) — answers for the router additions
1. Failure modes: dead registry path (flag+digest line, no crash); route button on
   expired/missing pending (polite decline, offset advances — R2-1 pattern); registry
   file empty/comments-only (v1 fallback); name collision between projects (first match
   wins, documented); seed race (atomic write).
2. Resume/kill: registry writes atomic (tmp+mv); route-pending survives restarts;
   offset discipline unchanged (advance after durable handling).
3. Ladder: sends keep tg_api's ≤2 retries; registry ops are local fs (no ladder needed —
   failure is loud via fatal/log).
4. Logs: every router action logs project + outcome; nothing new reads secrets.
5. Secrets: token path only, unchanged; new files (registry, route-pending) carry paths
   and labels, never tokens — negative grep extended over new scenario transcripts.
6. Idempotency: register twice = one line (grep -qxF); unregister missing = no-op with
   honest line; seed only when absent.
7. Question inventory: kit stays at NINE (short-circuit branch asks NOTHING new —
   inventory assert re-run green).
8. Real-data perimeter: all scenarios in mktemp sandboxes, isolated HOME + QROKY_REGISTRY.
9. Human hand-offs: Start press still human-only; apply-update auto-complete stops at
   the binding boundary (hint, not automation).

